Key Match Events: Mitchell Santner clinched 5 wickets including opener Max O'Dowd, dangerous Colin Ackermann and skipper Scott Edwards, leading New Zealand to a 99-run victory against Netherlands.
Rachin Ravindra grabbed a big wicket as he departed in-form Bas de Leede.
Matt Henry displayed the magic of his pace soon as he bowled out Vikramjit Singh.
Will Young, Rachin Ravindra and Tom Latham powered New Zealand to 322/7 after 50 overs.
Paul van Meekeren bowled a beautiful delivery to dismiss Daryl Mitchell while Bas de Leede departed Glenn Phillips.
New Zealand's Mitchell Santner is chosen as the Player of the match as he grabbed crucial 5 wickets during the match to derail the Netherlands batting.
Matt Henry took his 3rd wicket and bowled out Aryan Dutt, securing New Zealand's win by 99 runs.
Matt Henry clinched his second wicket, thanks to a wonderful low catch by Devon Conway.
Mitchell Santner took his 5th wicket by dismissing Ryan Klein.
Mitchell Santner single-handedly destroyed Netherlands batting by dismissing opener Max O'Dowd, Colin Ackermann, skipper Scott Edwards, and Roelof van der Merwe.
Teja Nidamanuru was run-out due to bad coordination between Colin Ackermann and Teja Nidamanuru.
